metrics_conclusion: In terms of chords and melody, Hallucinate is significantly more complex than the typical song, having above average scores in Chord Complexity, Melodic Complexity, Chord-Melody Tension, Chord Progression Novelty and Chord-Bass Melody.
key_conclusion:
Hallucinate is written in the key of B♭ Mixolydian.  

According to the Theorytab database, it is the 8th most popular key among Mixolydian keys and     the 39th most popular  among all keys. The B♭ Mixolydian scale is similar to the B♭ Major scale except that its 7th note (A♭) is a half step lower.  Mixolydian chord progressions are heavily featured in many genres of music like classic rock, which relies on the major chord built on the 7th scale degree. 

See the B♭ Mixolydian Cheat Sheet for popular chords, chord progressions, downloadable midi files and more!

metadata.editComments: Reverted to previous version. The chords were correct before.

The key is Bb Mixolydian. The key cannot be Bb Minor because the 1 chord is a major chord, even when all the Ds in the melody are flatted. If you look at other songs in Mixolydian you will see that they sometimes flat the 6 chord and do that with the melody. Look at "Shut Up and Drive" by Rihanna, for example.
